text: Sandusky is a city in the U.S. state of Ohio and the county seat of Erie County. According to 2020 census, the city had a population of 25,095. In 2011, Sandusky was ranked No. 1 by Forbes as the "Best Place to Live Cheaply" in the United States. ==References== Category:Cities in Ohio Category:County seats in Ohio
title: Sandusky, Ohio
